SIMPLE: adjournment
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adjournment
<hw>Ad*journ"ment</hw> <pr>(-m⟦eit⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. f.
<ets>adjournement</ets>, OF. <ets>ajornement</ets>. See
<er>Adjourn</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of adjourning; the
putting off till another day or time specified, or without
day.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The time or interval during which a public body
adjourns its sittings or postpones business.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adjudge</ent>⟦br⟧
